OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Reg Charles
OL,5,FHe said: "Soon after D-Day I went over
OL,6,Fto France on a troop ship from
OL,7,FSouthampton.
OL,9,F"Eventually I ended up with the 1st
OL,10,Fbattalion Ox and Bucks. I was in the
OL,11,F5th before. That disbanded though.
OL,13,F"We pushed our way through. It was
OL,14,Fpretty grim. There were dead bodies
OL,15,Fand animals. I was surprised at the
OL,16,Famount of animals the Germans used.
OL,18,F"Little carts which carried ammunition
OL,19,Fwere horse drawn and the horses were
OL,20,Ftrying to get through the same gates
OL,21,Fand just stood there and died.
